<subSubSection id="0D0B23FD35474D05370083EAEC9BDB02" pageId="0" pageNumber="207" type="notes">
<paragraph id="FA4B3DDDFDC706333B1A60417DDC4C53" pageId="0" pageNumber="207">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A02209FA85613C9290FE3DA0F4B27D5E" pageId="0" pageNumber="207">
The new species is more similar to 
<taxonomicName id="1151C2E8DE03659629AA14374CE64F94" genus="P." lsidName="P. crassifolia" pageId="0" pageNumber="207" rank="species" species="crassifolia">
<emphasis id="047A9264FDDBD8F97D89AAB93831E672" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="207">P. crassifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
than 
<taxonomicName id="3616009CCF5EB13DE100F850C45AFC36" genus="P." lsidName="P. neurophylla" pageId="0" pageNumber="207" rank="species" species="neurophylla">
<emphasis id="AB3BC858BBBE94FEF297E99DC7886615" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="207">P. neurophylla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Collett &amp; Hems1.) B.L. Burtt in its linear bracts (
<bibRefCitation id="BA64D7012B4F23094FD70D70549A3FA7" author="Wang, WT" editor="Wu, ZY" journalOrPublisher="18. Science Press, Beijing &amp; Missouri Botanical Garden Press, St. Louis" pageId="0" pageNumber="207" pagination="244 - 401" refId="B15" refString="Wang, WT, Pan, KY, Li, ZY, Weitzman, AL, Skog, LE, 1998. Gesneriaceae. In: Wu, ZY, Raven, PH, Eds., Flora of China, vol. 18. Science Press, Beijing &amp; Missouri Botanical Garden Press, St. Louis: 244 - 401" title="Gesneriaceae." volumeTitle="Flora of China, vol." year="1998">Wang et al. 1998</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="9438207BFFE3CB2DC62E52625A323C4B" author="Li, ZY" journalOrPublisher="Edinburgh Journal of Botany" pageId="0" pageNumber="207" refId="B9" refString="Li, ZY, Wang, YZ, 2004. Plants of Gesneriaceae in China. Henan Science and Technology Publishing House, Zhengzhou, 305-332." title="Plants of Gesneriaceae in China. Henan Science and Technology Publishing House, Zhengzhou, 305 - 332." year="2004">Li and Wang 2004</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="321D681FB2B4FBA6952018EC44B8605E" genus="P." lsidName="P. crassifolia" pageId="0" pageNumber="207" rank="species" species="crassifolia">
<emphasis id="85973D497FE25A435CAAD951F1444CAF" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="207">P. crassifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distributed in W Huibei, SE Chongqing, Guizhou, Guangxi and SE Yunnan in China, while 
<taxonomicName id="AC962C1092E2C8A406E5A368737E118E" genus="P." lsidName="P. neurophylla" pageId="0" pageNumber="207" rank="species" species="neurophylla">
<emphasis id="B4F7C396B8959C428462066F1305CCA5" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="207">P. neurophylla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distributed in China (Central and West Yunnan) and Myanmar. The new species is distributed in SE Yunnan and shares the similar distribution with 
<taxonomicName id="E187F4F370F3E85FA0AEE1D04C55CC71" genus="P." lsidName="P. crassifolia" pageId="0" pageNumber="207" rank="species" species="crassifolia">
<emphasis id="95A1D9A2A22EFBCA15CC5D55127D48FB" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="207">P. crassifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which is considered as the similar species to the new species. Besides, as to the small habit and fruits, it is somewhat similar to 
<taxonomicName id="52B537219405F199C6E2E9F29BD46798" genus="P." lsidName="P. velutina" pageId="0" pageNumber="207" rank="species" species="velutina">
<emphasis id="5664E5BD81D50758A5841F7A2F142AC2" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="207">P. velutina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in West Guangxi, which is next to SE Yunnan, but distinguished by corolla colour, size of calyx and corolla lobes, and twisted capsules (see the above diagnosis).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C0B16E59CC615565C1EAF58E3372DF37" pageId="0" pageNumber="207">
<bibRefCitation id="82B06956EE84BFACA7DF707D02B6120C" author="Vu, XP" journalOrPublisher="Guihaia" pageId="0" pageNumber="207" pagination="288 - 290" refId="B13" refString="Vu, XP, Do, TX, Wen, F, Wei, YG, 2011. Two occurrence taxa in Paraboea (C.B. Clarke) Ridl. (Gesneriaceae) for flora of Vietnam. Guihaia 31 (3): 288 - 290" title="Two occurrence taxa in Paraboea (C. B. Clarke) Ridl. (Gesneriaceae) for flora of Vietnam." volume="31" year="2011">Vu et al. (2011)</bibRefCitation>
reported 
<taxonomicName id="AB3448925B60D1EFF1C7696B10181244" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Gesneriaceae" genus="Paraboea" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Paraboea neurophylla" order="Lamiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="207" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="neurophylla">
<emphasis id="2573D33D23E7F5228B4B5868CF079707" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="207">Paraboea neurophylla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a new record in Vietnam. The voucher specimens are collected from Ba Be National Park, Bac Kan province, Vietnam. However, the figure (based on 
<emphasis id="FD4412F1E04ABA2C041C0EA2F3A4CD31" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="207">HLF 608</emphasis>
in HN) reveals that it seems to be conspecific with the new species we proposed here. Additionally, the description and geographical distribution of the new record in Vietnam roughly match that of the new species (
<bibRefCitation id="073AD50C9E8866B81B61A83BEF0139F2" author="Vu, XP" journalOrPublisher="Guihaia" pageId="0" pageNumber="207" pagination="288 - 290" refId="B13" refString="Vu, XP, Do, TX, Wen, F, Wei, YG, 2011. Two occurrence taxa in Paraboea (C.B. Clarke) Ridl. (Gesneriaceae) for flora of Vietnam. Guihaia 31 (3): 288 - 290" title="Two occurrence taxa in Paraboea (C. B. Clarke) Ridl. (Gesneriaceae) for flora of Vietnam." volume="31" year="2011">Vu et al. 2011</bibRefCitation>
). Although we are still waiting for further confirmation from the detailed surveys, it is possible that the new species will also occur in North Vietnam. In fact, 
<taxonomicName id="73BE5643D3697FC5E8AEB539B064B014" genus="P." lsidName="P. neurophylla" pageId="0" pageNumber="207" rank="species" species="neurophylla">
<emphasis id="6DD6D9AA79F19822F0DCB42DDF01C344" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="207">P. neurophylla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
grows at ca. 2000 m elevation in China (Yunnan, e.g. 
<emphasis id="61C4429AB17D634A59286B79F4338597" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="207">B.Y. Qiu 55121</emphasis>
in PE, 
<emphasis id="A72D8E4201CBBE79036B8FA74C0FB0AE" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="207">P. I Mao 1322</emphasis>
in PE, 
<emphasis id="229FA5FEB48209F5E2EA904D430EB916" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="207">S. E. Liu 831, 13970, 14087, 19713 and 20886</emphasis>
in PE, 
<emphasis id="FEB0DBA233ED5386B957189C6B339D64" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="207">K.M. Feng 10115</emphasis>
in PE, 
<emphasis id="06670F38D3A4D9B76AE52626EA176523" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="207">K.Y. Pan 1</emphasis>
in PE, 
<emphasis id="3FA4AE0836B83DB724883D6EFE410E35" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="207">J. Wu WJ2015010</emphasis>
in PE, 
<emphasis id="DE37098F4F2D5DFAA3ED3E8045F7DF06" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="207">Z.J. Qiu QZJ-0936</emphasis>
in PE, 
<emphasis id="183EF1CB081AE57EEFC6E0735BF4BE18" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="207">C.J. Chen 38</emphasis>
in PE, 
<emphasis id="3272CF69C4016EE64140001FBAB3F6A1" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="207">J.S. Xin 51404</emphasis>
in IBSC) and Myanmar (Shan hills, 
<emphasis id="717CB3BBB92D15CD59DF7B797B4A4160" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="207">Collett 804</emphasis>
, holotype K and isotype in E), but its habitat is very different from the habitat of the new species at less than 1000 m elevation (
<bibRefCitation id="7B84F58EDE307401030D485570FBFFDA" author="Wang, WT" editor="Wang, WT" journalOrPublisher="Science Press, Beijing" pageId="0" pageNumber="207" pagination="460 - 472" refId="B14" refString="Wang, WT, 1990. Gesneriaceae. In: Wang, WT, Ed., Flora Reipublicae Popularis Sinicae 69. Science Press, Beijing: 460 - 472" title="Gesneriaceae." volumeTitle="Flora Reipublicae Popularis Sinicae 69." year="1990">Wang 1990</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="1B8BFB3188C95390FF03D27D56F5579A" author="Wang, WT" editor="Wu, ZY" journalOrPublisher="18. Science Press, Beijing &amp; Missouri Botanical Garden Press, St. Louis" pageId="0" pageNumber="207" pagination="244 - 401" refId="B15" refString="Wang, WT, Pan, KY, Li, ZY, Weitzman, AL, Skog, LE, 1998. Gesneriaceae. In: Wu, ZY, Raven, PH, Eds., Flora of China, vol. 18. Science Press, Beijing &amp; Missouri Botanical Garden Press, St. Louis: 244 - 401" title="Gesneriaceae." volumeTitle="Flora of China, vol." year="1998">Wang et al. 1998</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="4640C35219CED1C844F1726541F94235" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1017/S0960428608005106" author="Xu, ZR" journalOrPublisher="Edinburgh Journal of Botany" pageId="0" pageNumber="207" pagination="161 - 347" refId="B20" refString="Xu, ZR, Burtt, BL, Skog, LE, Middleton, DJ, 2008. A revision of Paraboea (Gesneriaceae). Edinburgh Journal of Botany 65 (2): 161 - 347, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1017/S0960428608005106" title="A revision of Paraboea (Gesneriaceae)." url="https://doi.org/10.1017/S0960428608005106" volume="65" year="2008">Xu et al. 2008</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
